title: The Long Goodbye Syndrome
description: Jay makes a rookie mistake and it costs him. An Alien race of slug-like beings want him dead! It's up to his partner Kay to make things right and save him from annihilation.

title: The Irritable Bow-Wow Syndrome
description: A device that can generate two-mile-wide black holes has been stolen, activated, timed... and ends up getting eaten by Frank the Pug.

title: The Alpha Syndrome
description: K's mentor Alpha, a renegade agent who combined his body with alien organs, returns to menace K and procure an alien's heart.

title: The Head Trip Syndrome
description: Someone is messing with MIB's past to make sure they have no future!

title: The Elle of My Dreams Syndrome
The Take No Prisoners Syndrome
description: Prisoners breaks out of MIB, with only Jay and the worms to form a plan.

title: The Little Big Man Syndrome
description: Jay shrinks to help a tiny alien race but finds problems when needing to go back to his normal size.

title: The Black Christmas Syndrome
description: When Drekk kidnaps Santa Claus, MiB must save Christmas.

title: The I Want My Mummy Syndrome
The J Is for James Syndrome
description: After one maverick incident too many, Agent J is expelled from MiB and has his memories erased - most of them, as a recurring vision of the bugs gets him back.

title: The Circus Parade Syndrome
description: An alien who hid from an alien gang in a circus seeks help from MiB when the gang returns to capture him.
